.TH "CIRCLECI-MIGRATE" "1" "Jun 2026" "circleci-migrate" "CircleCI Org Migration CLI"

.SH NAME
circleci-migrate-secrets-decrypt - Decrypt an age-encrypted secret bundle.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcircleci-migrate secrets decrypt --identity-file  [-o ]  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
decrypt decrypts an age-encrypted bundle produced by 'secrets extract --encrypt'
or 'secrets capture --encrypt' into a plaintext secrets.json file.

.PP
The --identity-file flag accepts either:
  - An SSH private key file (OpenSSH format, ed25519 or RSA)
  - An age identity file (AGE-SECRET-KEY-1...)

.PP
The decrypted bundle is written to --output (default: secrets.json).

.PP
SECURITY: The output file contains plaintext secrets. Protect it, do not
commit it to version control, and delete it once the sync is complete.

.PP
Examples:
  circleci-migrate secrets decrypt --identity-file ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 bundle.age
  circleci-migrate secrets decrypt --identity-file identity.age -o secrets.json bundle.age


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for decrypt

.PP
\fB--identity-file\fP=""
	Path to an SSH private key or age identity file for decryption (required)

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="secrets.json"
	Path to write the decrypted bundle


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug logging

.PP
\fB--dest-token\fP=""
	API token for the destination org (env: CIRCLECI_DEST_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--host\fP="https://circleci.com"
	CircleCI host URL (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_HOST or CIRCLECI_HOST)

.PP
\fB--source-token\fP=""
	API token for the source org (env: CIRCLECI_SOURCE_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	Personal API token — fallback for both orgs (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_TOKEN)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcircleci-migrate-secrets(1)\fP
